w list of individuals was nominated, [[Geoff Neale]] was elected chair. [[R. Lee Wrights]] was elected Vice Chair, [[Ruth Bennett]] Secretary, and Tim Hagan Treasurer. Elected as national committee members-at-large were [[Bill Redpath]], Michael Cloud, Arvin Vohra, and [[Wayne Allyn Root]].<ref>[[Richard Winger|Winger, Richard]] (May 6, 2012) [http://www.ballot-access.org/2012/05/06/libertarian-party-takes-two-days-to-choose-party-officers/ \"Libertarian Party Takes Two Days to Choose Party Officers\"], ''[[Ballot Access News]]''.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Gary Johnson presidential campaign, 2012]]\n*[[Libertarian National Convention]]\n*Other parties' [[United States presidential nominating convention|presidential nominating conventions]] of 2012:\n**[[2012 Democratic National Convention|Democratic]]\n**[[2012 Green National Convention|Green]]\n**[[2012 Republican National Convention|Republican]]\n*[[Libertarian Party of Nevada]]\n*[[U.S. presidential election, 2012]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120509083125/http://www.libertywillwin.com/ Libertarian National 2012 Convention], official site\n\n{{United States presidential election, 2012}}\n{{Libertarian Party (United States)}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Libertarian Party (United States) National Conventions]]\n[[Category:2012 United States presidential election|Libertarian]]\n[[Category:Gary Johnson]]\n[[Category:2012 in Nevada|Libertarian National Convention]]\n[[Category:Political conventions in Nevada]]\n[[Category:History of Las Vegas]]\n[[Category:2012 conferences]]\n[[Category:May 2012 events in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Sal2100", "label": "safe", "comment": "update on the page link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_Libertarian_National_Convention"}
